{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d985975c-8d11-419a-9cb3-9a04543070db","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed *before* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_SMLZZB8HY1JGYlh0t9znvL","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-2a12b37484cb4d859d66c3ddcdce23cb/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-2a12b37484cb4d859d66c3ddcdce23cb/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"f67c904d-ad4f-4f5b-b828-0c3f90d6060d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters - files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nIn the `.fsproj`, the order is:\n1. Services.fs\n2. Domain.fs\n3. Program.fs\n\nBut `Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, which is defined in `Domain.fs`. Since `Domain.fs` comes after `Services.fs` in the compilation order, this will fail.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. Domain.fs (defines types)\n2. Services.fs (uses Domain types)\n\n\n3. Program.fs (depends on both)\n\nNow I need to reorder the files in the `.fsproj` to fix this.","outputTokens":466,"requestId":"1915:3AC5E4:1434B9D:16912A3:6A066F08"},"id":"af82a059-fe2c-4da7-8a32-9c47d970f984","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:55:44.470Z","parentId":"9a27ff69-b6d7-48c3-869f-50973ad73329"}
